title: Google\Cloud\Translate\V3\BatchTranslateTextRequest
name: BatchTranslateTextRequest
description:
The batch translation request.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.translation.v3.BatchTranslateTextRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. Location to make a call. Must refer to a caller's project. Format: projects/{project-number-or-id}/locations/{location-id}. The global location is not supported for batch translation. Only AutoML Translation models or glossaries within the same region (have the same location-id) can be used, otherwise an INVALID_ARGUMENT (400) error is returned.

params.name: data.target_language_codes
params.description: Required. Specify up to 10 language codes here.

params.name: data.models
params.description: Optional. The models to use for translation. Map's key is target language code. Map's value is model name. Value can be a built-in general model, or an AutoML Translation model. The value format depends on model type: - AutoML Translation models: projects/{project-number-or-id}/locations/{location-id}/models/{model-id} - General (built-in) models: projects/{project-number-or-id}/locations/{location-id}/models/general/nmt, If the map is empty or a specific model is not requested for a language pair, then default google model (nmt) is used.

params.name: data.input_configs
params.description: Required. Input configurations. The total number of files matched should be <= 100. The total content size should be <= 100M Unicode codepoints. The files must use UTF-8 encoding.

params.name: data.output_config
params.description: Required. Output configuration. If 2 input configs match to the same file (that is, same input path), we don't generate output for duplicate inputs.

params.name: data.glossaries
params.description: Optional. Glossaries to be applied for translation. It's keyed by target language code.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Optional. The labels with user-defined metadata for the request. Label keys and values can be no longer than 63 characters (Unicode codepoints), can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. Label values are optional. Label keys must start with a letter. See https://cloud.google.com/translate/docs/advanced/labels for more information.

methods.name: getModels
methods.description:
Optional. The models to use for translation. Map's key is target language code. Map's value is model name. Value can be a built-in general model, or an AutoML Translation model.

The value format depends on model type:

  • AutoML Translation models: projects/{project-number-or-id}/locations/{location-id}/models/{model-id}
  • General (built-in) models: projects/{project-number-or-id}/locations/{location-id}/models/general/nmt, If the map is empty or a specific model is not requested for a language pair, then default google model (nmt) is used.
